<p>Dr. Samir Mahmoud is currently Academic Director of <a href="https://www.usul.academy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Usul Academy</a>. Recently he was Assistant Professor at the Lebanese American University. He has a BA (Hons) in Anthropology &amp; Politics with a focus on multicultural theory and comparative religion, and an MA in Architectural History, Theory &amp; Urban Design with a focus on the traditional townscape from the University of New South Wales, Sydney Australia. He also holds an MPhil in Theology &amp; Religious Studies with a focus on comparative philosophy and aesthetics. He completed a PhD in Islamic Studies from the University of Cambridge.</p>
